def: A term of reproach for a low or vulgar labor person. [Slang]
A marquisate. [Obs.] "Nobles of the marquisdom of Saluce."Holinshed.
A denial. [R.] "Absolute renegation of Christ." Milman.
Of or pertaining to a cantor; as, the cantoris side of a choir;a cantoris stall. Shipley.
Destitute of pores; very close or compact in texture; solid.Sir T. Browne.
The white polar (Populus alba).Six abeles i' the churchyard grow. Mrs. Browning.
The officer in a religious house who had the care of theinfirmary. [Obs.]
Belonging to the Moesogoths, a branch of the Goths who settledin Moesia.
